    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Turn every FAQ row into a numbered Q/A block for the LLM.\n// Flexible about column names so it works with most spreadsheet layouts.\nconst rows = $input.all().map(i => i.json);\n\nfunction pick(row, keys) {\n  for (const k of Object.keys(row)) {\n    const norm = k.toLowerCase().trim();\n    if (keys.includes(norm)) return row[k];\n  }\n  return undefined;\n}\n\nconst faqText = rows.map((r, idx) => {\n  const cat = pick(r, ['category', 'topic', 'type']);\n  const q = pick(r, ['question', 'query', 'q', 'questions']) ?? Object.values(r)[0];\n  const a = pick(r, ['answer', 'response', 'a', 'answers']) ?? Object.values(r)[1];\n  const catStr = cat ? ` [${cat}]` : '';\n  return `${idx + 1}.${catStr} Q: ${q}\\n   A: ${a}`;\n}).join('\\n');\n\nconst prep = $('Prepare Input').first().json;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    faqText: faqText || 'No FAQ rows were found in the spreadsheet.',\n    faqRowCount: rows.length,\n    query: prep.query,\n    learnerName: prep.learnerName,\n    learnerEmail: prep.learnerEmail,\n    sessionId: prep.sessionId,\n    timestamp: prep.timestamp\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "447f5f2d-f240-43a2-81c8-2bfb1f38f97b",
      "name": "Build FAQ Context",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -784,
        96
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsonSchemaExample": "{\n  \"category\": \"course_access\",\n  \"intent\": \"Learner cannot log in to access their purchased course\",\n  \"needs_human\": false,\n  \"confidence\": 0.9,\n  \"answer\": \"Hi! Sorry you're having trouble logging in. Please try the 'Forgot Password' link on the login page to reset your password, and make sure you're using the same email you purchased with. If it still doesn't work, reply here and we'll dig deeper.\"\n}"
      },
      "id": "61eda438-43f7-4c0b-b137-29d433da12f8",
      "name": "FAQ Output Parser",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.outputParserStructured",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        -416,
        320
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are the AI Support Agent for CodeBasics, an online ed-tech platform that sells self-paced data/AI/coding courses and runs live cohorts.\n\nAnswer the learner's question using ONLY the FAQ knowledge base below. Be friendly, concise and helpful.\n\n=== FAQ KNOWLEDGE BASE ===\n{{ $json.faqText }}\n=== END FAQ ===\n\nLEARNER QUERY:\n\"{{ $json.query }}\"\n\nClassify the query into one of:\ncourse_access, certificate, refund, discount_sale, course_guidance, payment_issue, other.\n\nSet needs_human = true ONLY for genuine edge cases that the FAQ cannot safely resolve:\n- Billing disputes, or \"payment failed but money was deducted / not refunded\"\n- Real technical bugs the FAQ does not cover\n- Partnership / legal / account-specific issues not covered by the FAQ\n- Any query where the FAQ has no confident answer (confidence < 0.5)\n\nFor everything else (login/course access, certificate download, standard refund-policy questions, discounts/sales, course guidance), set needs_human = false and write the answer directly from the FAQ.\n\nIf needs_human is true, still write a short, polite holding message in the 'answer' field telling the learner their request is being escalated to a human.",
        "hasOutputParser": true
      },
      "id": "08d6810c-6f0a-4ea2-8711-aa542ffe46b8",
